def: Provided with a step or steps; having a series of offsets orparts resembling the steps of stairs; as, a stepped key. Steppedgear, a cogwheel of which the teeth cross the face in a series ofsteps.
Of superior excellence; having qualities to be boasted of.[Colloq.]One of our crack speakers in the Commons. Dickens.
A tribe of bivalve mollusks, characterized by the closed stateof the mantle which envelops the body. The ship borer (Teredonavalis) is an example.
The wife or widow of a duke; also, a lady who has thesovereignty of a duchy in her own right.
The act of helping or aiding; help. [Obs.] Bailey.
To paint; to cover or color with, or as with, paint.Else would a maiden blush bepaint my cheek. Shak.
To break up the camp of; to dislodge from camp. [R.]If they could but now uncamp their enemies. Milton.
